<font color="#FF0000">TO:  TOM AND ART...AND  OTHERS</font><br>
<tt>Wed Jul 23  4:47:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
&quot;Charlie&quot;<br><br>
His hands and feet were bound with wire,<br>
as he lay on his wounded side.<br>
I watched his blood turn the dust into mire, <br>
as my anger began to subside.<br><br>
He was no longer the hated foe I despised, <br>
but instead a disarmed and dying &quot;Cong.&quot;<br>
The loss of blood and the look in his eyes<br>
told me that he was not to live for long.<br><br>
I reached inside his filthy shirt <br>
and brought forth his meaning for life.<br>
Deep within me rose a terrible hurt<br>
from the picture of his kids and his wife.<br><br>
I held it up for quite a while,<br>
a humane and compassionate sign.<br>
He managed to offer a feeble smile,<br>
as I showed him a picture of mine.<br><br>
At last he hearkened to death's final call<br>
and succumbed to his tragic end.<br>
Now, I wonder if it mattered any at all<br>
that he thought of me as a friend.<br><br>
From &quot;Scars and Stripes, Forever&quot; copyrite 1990 by Edward Ramon
